{
    "level": "sentence",
    "abstract": [
        {
            "text": "Exotic charmonium-like states have been observed by various experiments over the last 15 years, but their nature is still under discussion. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Photo-(muo)production is a new promising instrument to study them. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "COMPASS, a fixed target experiment at CERN, analyzed the full set of the data collected with a muon beam between 2002 and 2011, covering the range from 7 GeV to 19 GeV in the centre-of-mass energy of the virtual photon-nucleon system. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "A signal in the mass spectrum of J/\u03c8\u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 with the statistical significance of 4.1 \u03c3 was observed in the reaction \u00b5 + N \u2192 \u00b5 + (J/\u03c8\u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 )\u03c0 \u00b1 N . ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Its mass and width are consistent with those of the X(3872). ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The shape of the \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 mass distribution from the observed decay into J/\u03c8\u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 is different from previous observations for X (3872). ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The observed signal may be interpreted as possible evidence of a new charmonium state X(3872). ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "It could be associated with a neutral partner of X(3872) with C = \u22121 predicted by a tetraquark model.",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        }
    ],
    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "Introduction",
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Over the last years a lot of new charmonium-like hadrons, so-called the XYZ states, at the mass range above 3.8 GeV/c 2 were discovered. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Several interpretations of the new states do exist: pure quarkonia, tetraquarks, hadronic molecules, hybrid mesons with a gluon content, etc. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "But at the moment many basic parameters of the XYZ states have not been determined yet. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "New experimental input is required to distinguish between the models that provide different interpretations of the nature of exotic charmonia. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The search for exotic charmonium-like states in exclusive photoproduction reactions was for the first time proposed in [1,2,3].",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 119,
                    "end": 122,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "[1,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 122,
                    "end": 124,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b1",
                    "text": "2,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 124,
                    "end": 126,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b2",
                    "text": "3]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "COMPASS, a fixed-target experiment at a secondary beam of SPS at CERN [4,5], already searched for photo(lepto-)production of the state Z \u00b1 c (3900) in the charge-exchange reaction \u00b5 + N \u2192 \u00b5 + Z \u00b1 (3900) c N using the experimental data obtained for positive muons of 160 GeV/c (2002-2010) or 200 GeV/c momentum (2011) scattering off solid 6 LiD (20026 LiD ( -2004 or NH 3 targets (2006-2011) [6]. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 70,
                    "end": 73,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b3",
                    "text": "[4,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 73,
                    "end": 75,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b4",
                    "text": "5]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 338,
                    "end": 349,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "text": "6 LiD (2002"
                },
                {
                    "start": 349,
                    "end": 362,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "text": "6 LiD ( -2004"
                },
                {
                    "start": 391,
                    "end": 394,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b5",
                    "text": "[6]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 7,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "COMPASS",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The search for muoproduction of the X(3872) in exclusive reactions is the continuation of these studies.",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The exotic hadron X(3872) was discovered by the Belle collaboration in 2003 [7]. ",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 76,
                    "end": 79,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b6",
                    "text": "[7]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Its mass is 3871.69 \u00b1 0.17 MeV/c 2 that is very close to the D 0D * 0 threshold. ",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The decay width of this state has not been determined yet, only an upper limit for the natural width \u0393 X(3872) of about 1.2 MeV/c 2 (CL=90%) exists. ",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The quantum numbers J P C of the X(3872) were determined by   LHCb to be 1 ++ [8,9]. ",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 78,
                    "end": 81,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b7",
                    "text": "[8,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 81,
                    "end": 83,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b8",
                    "text": "9]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Approximately equal probabilities to decay into J/\u03c83\u03c0 and J/\u03c82\u03c0 final states indicate large isospin symmetry breaking. ",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Lepto(photo-)production of the X(3872) at COMPASS was searched for in the exclusive charge-exchange reaction \u00b5",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The invariant mass spectrum of the J\u03c8\u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 subsystem is shown in Fig. 1 (two entries per event). ",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 67,
                    "end": 73,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_0",
                    "text": "Fig. 1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "It demonstrates two peaks whose positions and widths seem to suggest the production and decay of the \u03c8(2S) and X(3872) states. ",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The statistical significance of the second peak is 4.1\u03c3 that includes also systematic effects. ",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Nevertheless, it was also found that the shape of the invariant mass distribution for \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 corresponding to the second peak looks very different from previous results obtained for X(3872) by Belle, CDF, CMS and ATLAS (see Fig. 2) and is inconsistent with quantum numbers 1 ++ .",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 225,
                    "end": 231,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_1",
                    "text": "Fig. 2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "We have to conclude that the observed signal is not the well-known X(3872) but a new charmonium state X(3872) that could be interpreted within the tetraquark model of Refs. ",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "[10,11] which predicts a neutral partner of X(3872) that has the similar mass, negative C-parity, and decays into J/\u03c8\u03c3. ",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 4,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b9",
                    "text": "[10,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 4,
                    "end": 7,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b10",
                    "text": "11]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The mass of the new resonance is estimated as M X(3872) = 3860.0 \u00b1 10.4",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "MeV/c 2 and the Breit-Wigner width is \u0393 X(3872) < 51 MeV/c 2 (CL=90%). ",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The cross section of the reaction \u03b3N \u2192 N X(3872)\u03c0 \u00b1 multiplied by the branching fraction for the decay X(3872) \u2192 J/\u03c8\u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 was found to be 71 \u00b1 28 stat \u00b1 39 syst pb in the covered kinematic range with the mean value of \u221a s \u03b3N = 14 GeV.",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Lepto(photo-)production of the X(3872) was searched for also in the exclusive neutral reaction \u00b5 + N \u2192 \u00b5 + N X(3872) \u2192 \u00b5 + N J/\u03c8\u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 . ",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The invariant mass spectrum of the J\u03c8\u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 final state is shown in Fig. 3. ",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 69,
                    "end": 75,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "Fig. 3"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "It demonstrates only a peak from photo-diffractive production of \u03c8(2S) while there is no statistically significant signal at around M = 3872 MeV/c 2 . ",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The upper limit of the X(3872) production cross section in this reaction multiplied by the branching fraction for the decay X(3872) \u2192 J/\u03c8\u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 was established to be below 2.9 pb (CL=90%).",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "More detailed information on the search for muoproduction of X(3872) at COMPASS can be found in [12].  ",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 96,
                    "end": 100,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b11",
                    "text": "[12]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "(3900)N'",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Br, pb \u00d7 \u03c3 Figure 4. ",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 11,
                    "end": 19,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "Figure 4"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Estimated rates of photoproduction of exotic charmonia obtained by COMPASS (faint) or based on COMPASS results (dark).",
            "section": "Exclusive muoproduction of X(3872)",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "entity_spans": [
